  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nIn our solidity `0.5` compiler fork we [had a warning message](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/solidity/blob/6c323a9bcbc43ea551b2b950cef9e02d6d267420/libsolidity/parsing/Parser.cpp#L510-L513) which explained there are potential downsides to having constructor arguments in the OVM.  Unfortunately, when we moved to 0.6, the `isConstructor` property was removed and we [took out the warning](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/solidity/blob/e625624a7d971c0384ed4be149569c5e4b0c4c6e/libsolidity/parsing/Parser.cpp#L557-L561).\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nThere must be some other place where we can slot in a check that the constructor takes in arguments, and throw a similar warning if so.  We should do it!\r\n",
